snippet.textDisplay: I bet there is something off with the spark cut when shifting to 4th in your calibration. You know when you were setting the angles for each gear on the computer. I noticed that every time it went into 4th you were actually holding the lever back longer than every other gear change. It may not seem like it when you’re racing but it is happening. I believe this little bit of time is allowing the engine speed to come down some so that the next gear can completely engage (the whole reason for the spark cut in the first place)
